other_tests.findings: Dependent subsegmental atelectasis at the lung bases; a 4-mm hypodensity in the right lobe of the liver likely a cyst; gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and bilateral adrenal glands are normal; kidneys enhance and excrete contrast; no hydronephrosis or hydroureter; normal opacified stomach and intra-abdominal loops of bowel; no free air or fluid; wall thickening and free fluid at the junction of the descending and sigmoid colon; a tiny focus of gas possibly indicating a contained rupture; small amount of free fluid within the dependent portion of the pelvis; no lymphadenopathy meeting criteria for pathologic enlargement.
